stylometry: the obejectives of set covering models is to assign each member of a set 1 and match them with the least amount of members in the set 2.  We are trying to minimize the number of people or whatever we are working with in set 2, to cover all of the numbers in set 1.  The fixed cost model is a model in which we are given costs that are fixed and do not change and we have to come up with ways that change our target cells based on the costs or other fixed expenses.  An example of a set covering model is if we have a set of numbers (which is set 1) that stand for certain products and we have a set of numbers (which is set 2) that determines the amount of workers we have for these products (in set 1).  The goal of a set covering model is to determine how to use the amount of workers in set 2 to minimize the workers needed to cover all of the products in set 1.
